<doc id="1031144" wikidata="Q317376" url="?curid=1031144" title="Kinney Lake">
<text>Kinney Lake is a lake located in Mount Robson Provincial Park of British Columbia, Canada. The lake can be reached by following the Berg Lake Trail for . The lake is an expansion of the Robson River (a tributary of the upper Fraser River) and is located about halfway between the river&#x27;s source and its mouth. It was named by Arthur Philemon Coleman, Canadian geologist, who explored the region with his friend, George Kinney, who spotted the lake first.

== See also ==

*List of lakes of British Columbia
*Robson Lake

